title: Sydney woman pretends to be single mum for rental subsidy
text: Muslim woman pretended to be a single mum for 18 YEARS to get welfare and live in a housing commission flat - but her husband was earning $1 MILLION a year Rebecca Khodragha posed as 'battling single mother' for 18 years to get welfare She married Khaled in an Islamic ceremony, but the wedding was unregistered The couple have been living in a Punchbowl housing commission since 1999 Documents uncovered Khaled earns $1 million each year in electrical business They also own two other Sydney properties, a Lakemba and a Greenacre unit
